# UIX/UI Creation Rules

You are creating a UIX/UI specification document. Follow these rules strictly.

## Required Inputs

Before creating a UIX-UI.md, you must have:
- Approved SPEC.md (@specs/XXX/SPEC.md) — for user stories and acceptance criteria
- Approved DESIGN.md (@specs/XXX/DESIGN.md) — for API specs, data models, system architecture
- Access to @.framework/CONSTITUTION.md for project standards (tech stack, component library, styling conventions, accessibility standards)

If SPEC.md is not approved (Status != APPROVED), STOP and inform the user.
If DESIGN.md is not approved (Status != APPROVED), STOP and inform the user.

## Template

Always use the template structure from @.framework/templates/UIX-UI.template.md

## Figma MCP Integration

When the developer provides Figma URLs, use Figma MCP tools to extract design data:

- `get_design_context` — extract component structure, layout, and hierarchy from Figma frames
- `get_variable_defs` — extract design tokens (colors, typography, spacing) defined as Figma variables
- `get_screenshot` — capture visual reference of specific frames or components
- `get_metadata` — retrieve file and frame metadata (names, IDs, last modified)
- `search_design_system` — search for specific components or patterns in the Figma design system

**Translation rule:** Figma output represents design intent. Translate it into the project's actual conventions per CONSTITUTION.md. For example:
- Figma color variables → project design system tokens
- Figma component names → project component library naming conventions
- Figma layout → project's responsive/grid system
- Figma typography → project's type scale

Do NOT copy Figma values verbatim if they conflict with CONSTITUTION.md conventions. The constitution is authoritative for implementation details.

**If no Figma URLs are provided:** Produce the UIX-UI artifact based on SPEC.md + DESIGN.md alone. Derive screen inventory from user stories, component hierarchy from the architecture, and data bindings from API endpoints. Note in the Overview: "No Figma designs provided — specifications derived from SPEC.md and DESIGN.md."

## Field Rules

### Metadata
- **ID**: Must match the SPEC.md ID exactly
- **Name**: Must match the SPEC.md Name exactly
- Status is always DRAFT until approved
- Author: developer name + "/ AI-assisted"
- Reviewer: leave blank
- Date: today's date

### Overview
- 1-2 paragraphs maximum
- Describe the UI approach and how the feature presents itself to the user
- Reference the tech stack and component library from CONSTITUTION.md
- If Figma was used, note: "Based on Figma designs from [URL]."
- If no Figma, note: "No Figma designs provided — specifications derived from SPEC.md and DESIGN.md."

### Screen Inventory
- Every user story from SPEC.md must map to at least one screen/view
- Include route/path for each screen (derive from DESIGN.md API routes or CONSTITUTION.md routing conventions)
- If a user story spans multiple screens, list each screen separately

### Component Specifications
- One section per screen from the Screen Inventory
- Component hierarchy shown as ASCII tree
- Every component must list: Props, State, and Data Binding (referencing DESIGN.md API endpoints)
- Use the component library/framework from CONSTITUTION.md (do not hardcode React, Vue, Angular, etc.)
- Component names must follow CONSTITUTION.md naming conventions

### Design Token Mapping
- If Figma tokens are available (via `get_variable_defs`), map each to the project's design system
- If no Figma data, write: "No Figma tokens provided — using project design system defaults from CONSTITUTION.md."
- Do NOT invent design tokens that aren't in Figma or CONSTITUTION.md

### Interaction Patterns
- **User Flows**: Primary flows through the screens, derived from SPEC.md user stories
- **Transitions**: Only specify custom transitions if Figma or requirements call for them
- **State Handling**: MUST include loading, empty, error, and success states for every screen that fetches data

### Responsive / Adaptive Layout
- Follow CONSTITUTION.md breakpoint conventions if defined
- If CONSTITUTION.md doesn't specify, derive from the project's CSS framework/system
- Write "Single layout — no responsive breakpoints required." only if the feature genuinely has no responsive needs

### Accessibility Requirements
- Apply CONSTITUTION.md accessibility standards to every component
- At minimum: ARIA roles/labels, keyboard navigation, focus management, color contrast
- If CONSTITUTION.md doesn't specify accessibility standards, apply WCAG 2.1 AA as the default

### Asset Inventory
- List all assets referenced in Figma (via `get_design_context` or `get_screenshot`)
- Include type (icon, image, illustration, font) and source
- If no external assets, write: "No external assets required."

### Open Questions
- Unresolved UI/UX decisions that need answers before task breakdown
- Format as checklist: `- [ ] Question here?`
- These must be resolved before moving to TASKS.md

## Constraints

- Every UI decision must align with CONSTITUTION.md (tech stack, component library, styling, accessibility)
- Do NOT hardcode framework-specific assumptions (no React JSX, no Vue templates, etc.) — use framework-agnostic component descriptions; CONSTITUTION.md determines the framework
- Do NOT include implementation code (belongs in actual code via tasks)
- Do NOT include task breakdown (belongs in TASKS.md)
- Do NOT contradict or expand scope beyond SPEC.md and DESIGN.md
- All bracket placeholders from template must be removed from output; if info is missing, add an Open Question instead

## Validation

Before completing, verify:
- [ ] Every user story from SPEC.md maps to at least one screen
- [ ] Every screen has a component hierarchy with props, state, and data bindings
- [ ] Data bindings reference actual API endpoints from DESIGN.md
- [ ] Loading, empty, error, and success states defined for data-fetching screens
- [ ] Accessibility requirements defined per component
- [ ] Design tokens mapped (from Figma) or defaults noted (from CONSTITUTION.md)
- [ ] No framework-specific code or markup in the document
- [ ] All required sections filled (no placeholders)
- [ ] Status set to DRAFT

## Output

Save the file to: `specs/XXX-{slug}/UIX-UI.md`

Must be in the same folder as the corresponding SPEC.md and DESIGN.md.
